The home features jerseys from both Russian and Argentine history as well as other displays. Russia's ambassador to Argentina, Viktor Koronelli, was joined by the president of Argentina's soccer association (AFA), Claudio "Chiqui" Tapa for the ribbon cutting. The World Cup, which will be hosted in 11 cities across Russia. President Vladimir Putin is hoping to use the World Cup, set to run from June 14 to July 15, to showcase Russia as a global superpower and reinvigorate areas of the country where the economy has stagnated with an influx of tourists and spending. --Reuters--